---
description: Stop existing dev server before starting a new one
alwaysApply: true
---

When launching the Next.js dev server:

1. **Always stop the old server first** — kill any process listening on the target port (default 3000) before starting a new instance.
2. **Use `npm run dev`** — the project script runs `scripts/dev.ps1`, which stops the port then starts `next dev`.
3. **Manual restarts** — if you start `next dev` directly, run the port kill step first:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  Select-Object -ExpandProperty OwningProcess -Unique |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_ -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
```

4. After large changes or stale `.next` cache errors, also remove `.next` before restarting.
